The paper deals with problems related to independent and dominating sets on interval graphs, which are commonly studied in the subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of vertex coloring and the concept of balanced sets suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the complexity analysis and algorithm design aspects of the paper may fall under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
